snippet.title: Bailey & Asa's PROPOSAL Video ‚ù§Ô∏è
snippet.description:
Watch as Asa PROPOSES to Bailey after they dated for over four years! He planned this all on his own, with some covert help from Brooklyn, family and friends. Bailey had no idea. What was your favorite part of the proposal? SUBSCRIBE and COMMENT BELOW!

‚úÖ Here is the ring Asa chose for Bailey from James Allen: üëâüèª https://bit.ly/3gacwM5

‚úÖ Be sure to follow us on Instagram to see MORE PROPOSAL PHOTOS and Stories! üëâüèª https://www.instagram.com/BrooklynAndBailey

I met Asa met five years ago WAY BACK in 2016 when I was only 16 and he was 15. I didn‚Äôt know it then, but I had just met my future husband! It took a year of him pursuing me, and me constantly putting him in the FRIEND ZONE, before I realized what a catch he really was! On Feb 25, 2017, Asa and I officially started dating, ending the day with my very first kiss! You can watch that video, HERE: https://youtu.be/FsI8KtveD3A (y‚Äôall prob know that storyüòâ)

In the beginning of this proposal video, there is a small outtake taken when Brooklyn and I were filming our music video for Simple Things in May, 2017. In that moment, Brooklyn and my mom had put Asa up to the task of pranking me with a fake wedding ring and proposal! Little did I know then that four years later Asa would be the one to OFFICIALLY propose to me... and I wouldn't have it ANY. OTHER. WAY! 

As Asa walked me out to where he planned to propose, I started bawling my eyes out when I figured out what was going on... I literally had NO clue! The date 4/3/21 will forever be a day to remember for the both of us.‚ù§Ô∏è It might seem small to you, but it was like even the world was counting down for us! 

I‚Äôm so glad I got to say YES to my forever! (I‚Äôm still having a hard time remembering to call Asa my fianc√© instead of boyfriend LOL!)

üíã's -Bailey

PS~ Special thanks to Lizzy McAlpine for lending us the use of her unreleased music, to our friend Antoine for taking photos and video, and Kamri for editing this proposal video! And be sure to check back NEXT WEEK for a longer BTS vlog of EVERYTHING leading up to the proposal!

Unpretentious yet expertly decorated, Troye collaborated with designer David Flack of local firm Flack Studio to bring the vision of his sunny, soulful home to life. An erstwhile brick factory and handball court, the property was transformed into a residence in 1970 by architect John Mockridge, preserving the essence of its Victorian-era origins. Today, it‚Äôs an eclectically decorated sanctuary - and a home for Troye‚Äôs artistic imagination.

snippet.title: F9 - Official Trailer 2
snippet.description:
F9
Fast is back June 25.
http://www.thefastsaga.com/

No matter how fast you are, no one outruns their past. 

F9 is the ninth chapter in the Fast & Furious Saga, which has endured for two decades and has earned more than $5 billion around the world.  

Vin Diesel‚Äôs Dom Toretto is leading a quiet life off the grid with Letty and his son, little Brian, but they know that danger always lurks just over their peaceful horizon. This time, that threat will force Dom to confront the sins of his past if he‚Äôs going to save those he loves most. His crew joins together to stop a world-shattering plot led by the most skilled assassin and high-performance driver they‚Äôve ever encountered: a man who also happens to be Dom‚Äôs forsaken brother, Jakob (John Cena, the upcoming The Suicide Squad).

snippet.title: Army of the Dead | Official Trailer | Netflix
snippet.description:
In Select Theaters May and on Netflix May 21.

From filmmaker Zack Snyder (300, Watchmen, Zack Snyder‚Äôs Justice League), ARMY OF THE DEAD takes place following a zombie outbreak that has left Las Vegas in ruins and walled off from the rest of the world. When Scott Ward (Dave Bautista), a former zombie war hero who‚Äôs now flipping burgers on the outskirts of the town he now calls home, is approached by casino boss Bly Tanaka (Hiroyuki Sanada), it‚Äôs with the ultimate proposition: break into the zombie-infested quarantine zone to retrieve $200 million sitting in a vault beneath the strip before the city is nuked by the government in 32 hours. With little left to lose, Ward takes on the challenge, assembling a ragtag team of experts for the heist. With a ticking clock, a notoriously impenetrable vault, and a smarter, faster horde of Alpha zombies closing in, only one thing‚Äôs for certain in the greatest heist ever attempted: survivors take all.
